ZCZC OE56
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 192300 UTC
A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND N ACROSS MUCH OF THE
PORTPATRICK AREA ON MONDAY EVENING BUT WITH FRONTAL
TROUGHS IN THE N BRINGING A MORE CYCLONIC FLOW ACROSS THE
FAR N. THE RIDGE IS THEN EXP TO DECLINE SEWARDS ON
TUESDAY AS FURTHER FRONTAL TROUGHS BRING A MORE GENERAL
CYCLONIC FLOW ACROSS THE AREA FM THE W DURING THE DAY.
INCRLY CYCLONIC CONDITIONS ACROSS THE AREA ARE THEN
SIGNALLED FOR WEDNESDAY AND THURSDAY WITH AREAS OF LOW
PRESSURE FCST TO MOV NE ACROSS NERN PARTS. WINDS ARE
LIKELY TO BECOME STRG AT TIMES ACROSS THE N AND W OF THE
PORTPATRICK AREA DURING TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY. CURRENT
INDICATIONS ARE THEN THAT NEAR GALE TO GALE FORCE WINDS
SPREAD TO SWERN PARTS EARLY ON THURSDAY AND TRANSFER N TO
LIE BETWEEN 57 N AND 60 N BY THURSDAY EVENING
NNNN